		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:22px;color:#00aeef"><strong>THE IMPACT OF NCS: IPSOS MORI'S FINDINGS</strong></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="center" valign="top"><img src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/staffing/Images/ncstc_hr_290914.jpg" width="550" height="22" border="0" style="display:block"></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:20px;color:#222222">
		
			<table width="550" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tbody><tr>
			
			<td align="left" valign="top"><p>We’ve been singing praises for the impact that The Challenge’s NCS programmes have had in the last couple of issues, but how has the Government’s NCS initiative actually changed social integration in the UK? Third Sector magazine recently published a report analysing the impact of National Citizen Service in 2013 and 2014. Key findings included:</p>

		<strong>•</strong> NCS generated 8 million extra volunteering hours in 2013 and 2014.<br>
		<strong>•</strong> NCS graduates continued to volunteer in their free time, even up to a year after finishing the programme.<br>
<strong>•</strong> In summer 2014, NCS delivered social benefits worth up to £252m, at the cost of £63.4m.<br>
		<strong>•</strong> In Nov 2015, the Government vowed to invest an additional £1.1bn to NCS.</p>


			<p><a href="http://www.thirdsector.co.uk/report-reveals-impact-national-citizen-service-scheme/volunteering/article/1377812
" target="_blank">Read the full article here!</a></p></td>
			
			</tr></tbody></table>
		</td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
