		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:20px;color:#222222">
		
			<table width="550" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tbody><tr>
			
			<td align="left" valign="top"><p>For 2016 we've vowed to make the NCS programme more accessible than ever to young people, regardless of their backgrounds or needs. Our dedicated Inclusion Staffing Team are rolling out the new <a href="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/opportunities/learning-and-behaviour-mento/" target="_blank"> Learning & Behaviour Mentor</a> role, and investing in the existing <a href="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/opportunities/support-worker/" target="_blank"> Support Worker</a> and <a href="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/opportunities/personal-coach/" target="_blank"> Personal Coach</a> roles more. This means:</p>

<strong>•</strong> NCS will be accessible to even more young people<br>
		<strong>•</strong> More specialist roles to suit candidates' skills & experience<br>
		<strong>•</strong> We'll be able to provide professional development to our seasonal staff focusing on behaviour management.</p>

			<p><strong>Think you'd suit these roles? <a href="https://staffing.the-challenge.org/Login.aspx?signup=1" target="_blank"> Then apply here!</a></p>
			</td>
			</tr></tbody></table>
		</td>
		
